# TypeScript — lib/

## Modules

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `prompts.ts` | AI system/user prompts |
| `groq.ts` | Groq client + model config |
| `normalize-ai.ts` | JSON parse, polarity, test case enrichment |
| `sample-requirements.ts` | 25 Quick Select workflows |
| `test-data-builder.ts` | Stage 4 synthetic data |
| `skeleton-builder.ts` | Stage 5 Playwright/API skeleton |
| `onboarding.ts` | Guide localStorage state |
| `guide-scripts.ts` | Alex dialogue lines |
| `clerk-appearance.ts` | Clerk dark theme object |

## Style

- Prefer explicit types for public exports; use `type` for unions (`CaseFilter`, `GuideScene`).
- No `any` unless unavoidable at JSON boundaries — narrow with guards in `normalize-ai.ts`.
- Pure functions where possible; side effects only in builders that need them.
